message.content:
cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper focuses on deep learning applications, specifically on generating efficient code for deep neural network models such as AlexNet and VGG-19. These models are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of deep learning frameworks and compilers, which are commonly used in AI applications.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper explores the use of the Sunway many-core processor, which is a highly parallel architecture. The authors leverage the architecture features during compilation to generate efficient code for deep learning applications.
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper focuses on generating efficient code for deep learning applications on the Sunway architecture. The authors compare the performance of their automatically generated code with hand-optimized OpenACC implementations.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes swTVM, an extension of the TVM deep learning compiler, to support ahead-of-time compilation for architectures requiring cross-compilation such as Sunway. The authors leverage the architecture features during compilation to generate efficient code for deep learning applications.
